<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="sa0981eg"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="sa" href="#sa0981eg">SA (VI.A) </a>: <a href="../../ff/fnbs/ssaall.htm#sa0981eg"> 981(eg)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> gugglet: <small>Red</small></blockquote> <dd class="well"> <ul class="list-inline" id="sa0981eg"><li>FW unlocated</li> </ul> <mm class="note">Note: See also: <a name="n03127g" href="n03all.htm#n03127g">N03 (VI.B.3):127(g)</a>, probable source of <cite>FW</cite> 31.11 Burton [1000 Nights and a Night] notes of &lsquo;gugglet&rsquo; &mdash; Arab. &ldquo;kullah&rdquo; (in Egypt pron. &ldquo;gulleh&rdquo;), the wide-mouthed jug, called in the Hijaz &ldquo;baradiyah;&rdquo; &ldquo;daurak&rdquo; being the narrow. These are used either for water or sherbet and, being made of porous clay, &ldquo;sweat,&rdquo; and keep the contents cool; hence all old Anglo-Egyptians drink from them, not from bottles. </mm> </dd></dl>
